sequenceDiagram
  %% Evidence: backend/src/routes/auth.rs, services/password.rs, services/jwt.rs, services/security.rs
  actor User
  participant Browser
  participant Auth as Auth routes
  participant Security as Password / login limiter
  participant DB as PostgreSQL
  participant JWT as JWT service

  alt Register
    User->>Browser: Submit email, password, name
    Browser->>Auth: POST /api/auth/register
    Auth->>Security: Validate and Argon2 hash
    Auth->>DB: Insert user, global role, default membership
  else Login
    User->>Browser: Submit email and password
    Browser->>Auth: POST /api/auth/login
    Auth->>DB: Count recent failed attempts and load active user
    Auth->>Security: Verify Argon2 password
    Auth->>DB: Record login result
  else Refresh
    Browser->>Auth: POST /api/auth/refresh with cookie or JSON token
    Auth->>DB: Require valid hash, active user, unexpired/unrevoked row
    Auth->>DB: Revoke presented refresh row
  end

  Auth->>JWT: Sign access token and generate refresh token
  Auth->>DB: Store refresh-token hash and expiry
  Auth-->>Browser: Access token, account/memberships, HttpOnly refresh cookie
  Note over Browser,Auth: Recovery, MFA, email verification, and atomic refresh rotation are not verified
